    "Label skew happens when certain labels are more prevalent on some devices than others, leading to an imbalance in the label distribution.",
    "For example, rice is commonly grown in Southeast Asia, whereas in drier areas like North America, such type of crop is mainly wheat.",
    "Generally, such imbalances can significantly affect the performance of DL models in federated learning, which may become biased towards the more prevalent classes.",
    "However, different from typical supervised tasks where the data is accompanied with fixed and explicit labels, we do not focus on label skew in this study for program repair task where the objective is to generate a valid patch that correctly fixes a bug.",
    "(2) Feature skew."
  ],
